HEADWORD: Centrical
<hw>Cen"tric*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <def>Placed in the center or middle;
central; situated at or near a center.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>At York or some other <qex>centrical</qex> place.</q> <rj><qau>Sir
W. Scott.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Cen"tric*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Cen"tric*al*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Centricity</ent>⟦br⟧
